I saw that! It definitely provides some depth and context. Also, you’re right there were a lot of commercials but still worth watching!

I grew up in Duluth,MN on Lake Superior where there is an abundance of Viking and Masonic history. When watching OI, I love daydreaming about what *could be* hidden on the shores of the Gitch.. Probably like most on this sub, I find Templar history to be fascinating already but as a little girl our family Parish attended mass at a cathedral that had a strong Knighthood presence with formal processions and rituals very openly and annually. It was such a production it’s stuck with me. Probably not surprising the whole cathedral was filled with Masonic/templar imagery on everything and the evolution from then to now is so interesting! 

Okay ramble over. If anyone has more content recommendations, send it!
